  <discussion>Distribution of Planodes virginicum is primarily in the southeastern and central
        United States (Virginia west into Kansas, south into Texas, and east into Florida). Its
        disjunction in southern California and northern Baja California suggests that it was
        introduced there. Considering the weedy nature of the species, I expect that its range
        extends beyond that given above.</discussion>
